[00:09.69]This old wood’s got scratches, stories in the grain
[00:13.46]Crumbs from yesterday, coffee rings and names
[00:17.23]Mail spread out beside a half-read verse
[00:20.99]Laundry folded slow while the pot still simmers
[00:24.76]Kids talk over grace, somebody rolls their eyes
[00:28.53]Life’s loud, life’s messy, but we bow our heads this time
[00:32.30]We don’t always agree
[00:36.07]We don’t always get it right
[00:39.83]But we keep coming back
[00:43.60]Every single night
[00:47.37]’Cause the dinner table’s holy ground
[00:51.14]Broken hearts and bread passed around
[00:54.91]We laugh, we cry, we pray it through
[00:58.67]Every seat tells a story too
[01:02.44]It’s where love learns how to stay
[01:06.21]Where forgiveness finds a way
[01:09.98]From our hands to Heaven’s will
[01:13.74]The table’s teaching us still
[01:17.51]Homework tears and wedding plans
[01:21.28]Hard conversations, holding hands
[01:25.05]Gossip whispered, truths confessed
[01:28.82]Joy laid bare, anger laid to rest
[01:32.58]Friends drop by, pull up a chair
[01:36.35]There’s always room, there’s always prayer
[01:40.12]If you’re hungry, you belong
[01:43.89]Doesn’t matter where you’re from
[01:47.66]Some nights it’s quiet
[01:51.42]Some nights it’s war
[01:55.19]But grace keeps walking
[01:58.96]Through the door
[02:02.73]’Cause the dinner table’s holy ground
[02:06.50]Where the lost get found
[02:10.26]We share the weight, we break the bread
[02:14.03]Say the things we left unsaid
[02:17.80]It’s where mercy meets our shame
[02:21.57]Where God knows us by our name
[02:25.34]Every tear, every meal
[02:29.10]The table makes us real
[02:32.87]Long ago, a table held the Son
[02:36.64]Bread was broken, love begun
[02:40.41]Not a throne, just open hands
[02:44.18]A promise sealed in a simple plan
[02:47.94]So we gather here the same
[02:51.71]In His likeness, in His name
[02:55.48]If He served and made room
[02:59.25]Then so will we—
[03:03.02]’Til He comes again
[03:06.78]Yeah the dinner table’s holy ground
[03:10.55]Grace enough to go around
[03:14.32]Every chair can hold one more
[03:18.09]Just like it did before
[03:21.86]From our chaos to His peace
[03:25.62]This is where we’re made complete
[03:29.39]In the breaking, in the sharing
[03:33.16]God is always there
[03:36.93]So pull up close, don’t stand alone
[03:40.70]This table feels like home
[03:44.46]Every meal, every prayer
[03:48.23]He’s already sitting there
